snippet.title: ML.NET End-to-End: Wine Regression with Database Data
snippet.description:
The first in a series of videos that goes end-to-end with an ML.NET model. This video goes over creating and using data in a database to create a model to predict wine quality and saves the data into Azure Blob Storage.

End-to-end 2: Web API video - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FFvpEeWW7AQ

Code - https://github.com/jwood803/MLNet-EndToEnd/blob/master/WineRegressionModel/Program.cs

Data - https://www.kaggle.com/rajyellow46/wine-quality

snippet.title: Create Your First Machine Learning Pipeline in ML.NET
snippet.description:
Update: The version of ML.NET in this video is quite old. For a more up-to-date version of this video check out this one - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mUUWfzsADVg

A brief introduction to creating your first machine learning pipeline in ML.NET. Companion video to this blog post - https://www.wintellect.com/machine-learning-c-introduction-ml-net/

The code is available here - https://github.com/Wintellect/DataScienceExamples/blob/master/ML.NET/MLNetExamples/BasicPipeline/Program.cs

And you can view the data available here - https://github.com/Wintellect/DataScienceExamples/tree/master/ML.NET/datasets

R Squared post - http://statisticsbyjim.com/regression/interpret-r-squared-regression/
